"{\"abstract\":\"We propose a general approach to modeling semi-supervised learning (SSL) algorithms. Specifically, we present a declarative language for modeling both traditional supervised classification tasks and many SSL heuristics, including both well-known heuristics such as co-training and novel domain-specific heuristics. In addition to representing individual SSL heuristics, we show that multiple heuristics can be automatically combined using Bayesian optimization methods. We experiment with two classes of tasks, link-based text classification and relation extraction. We show modest improvements on well-studied link-based classification benchmarks, and state-of-the-art results on relation-extraction tasks for two realistic domains.\",\"arxivId\":\"1703.01557\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"1996394\",\"name\":\"Lidong Bing\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1996394\"},{\"authorId\":\"50056360\",\"name\":\"William W. Cohen\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/50056360\"},{\"authorId\":\"34994191\",\"name\":\"Bhuwan Dhingra\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/34994191\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"47002659\",\"name\":\"Yanchao Li\"},{\"authorId\":\"1802530\",\"name\":\"Y. Wang\"},{\"authorId\":\"49595364\",\"name\":\"Cheng Bi\"},{\"authorId\":\"48324130\",\"name\":\"Xiaohui Jiang\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1016/j.knosys.2018.04.017\",\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"8d2c9c33adb7eb5229bee6687878c080749ed97f\",\"title\":\"Revisiting transductive support vector machines with margin distribution embedding\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/8d2c9c33adb7eb5229bee6687878c080749ed97f\",\"venue\":\"Knowl. Based Syst.\",\"year\":2018},{\"arxivId\":\"1804.09238\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"3456820\",\"name\":\"Haitian Sun\"},{\"authorId\":\"50056360\",\"name\":\"William W. Cohen\"},{\"authorId\":\"1996394\",\"name\":\"Lidong Bing\"}],\"doi\":nu